description._content: Catalog #: 09_01591 Title: Elwyn H. Gibbon Special Collection Photo Karachi India Date: 4/25/1905 Additional Information: Trucks, carts and a damaged Lockheed P-38 aircraft on dirt road, Elwyn Gibbon (b.1911 d.1942) was an American pilot who served as a pilot in the Chinese Air Force in the Foreign Volunteer Squadron. Later he served as a Vultee Aircraft Company test pilot in Karachi, India, where he died in a plane crash in 1942. Corporation Name: Lockheed Corporation Tags: Elwyn H.
